# Investment Frameworks

Before writing research (`{TICKER}/research/`), deep dives, portfolio scans, or cross-checks, read:

| File | Use when |
|------|----------|
| `_system/frameworks/decision_stack.md` | **Any research task** — unified pipeline (what → durable → payoff → return → stance) |
| `_system/frameworks/hohn_business_analysis.md` | **Every deep dive** — operating snapshot, thesis pillars, valuation bridge |
| `_system/frameworks/optionality_valuation.md` | **FRMO, MSB, KEWL, SJT** — floor + option / SOTP / HK royalty curve |
| `_system/frameworks/investment_process.md` | Workflow — discover → download → read → analyze → review |
| `_system/frameworks/archetype_models.json` | Tier 2 prompts by archetype |
| `_system/prompts/deep_dive_template.md` | Deep dive output shape |
| `_system/frameworks/mental_models.md` | Appendix — full model catalog + HK extracts |
| `_system/frameworks/lawrence_irr.md` | Appendix — 10yr IRR math detail |
| `_system/frameworks/quality_checklist.md` | Folded into decision stack Payoff & return section |
| `_system/frameworks/classification.md` | Field definitions + report footer |
| `_system/frameworks/ai_disruption_lens.md` | Holdings with AI exposure; daily portfolio scans |
| `_system/reference/investment-wisdom/INDEX.md` | Which genius lens applies to this ticker |

## Wisdom library (PDFs + HK extracts)

`_system/reference/investment-wisdom/` — Munger, Pabrai, Stahl, Horizon Kinetics. Cite by path when applying mental models.

| Genius | Folder | Apply when |
|--------|--------|------------|
| **Munger** | `munger/` | Inversion, psychology, moats, circle of competence |
| **Pabrai** | `pabrai/` | Dhando payoff, bet sizing, simplicity, partner-letter discipline |
| **Stahl** | `stahl/` | Croupiers, exchanges, real diversification, spinoffs |
| **Horizon Kinetics** | `horizon-kinetics/` | Equity yield curve, predictive attributes, time arbitrage |
| **Chris Hohn / TCI** | `tci/` | Operating mechanics, thesis pillars, valuation bridge |

Read relevant PDFs/extracts (or `_system/memory/MEMORY.md` approved beliefs for that genius) before deep dives — not from training memory alone.

## Read order for primary sources

1. Latest annual report
2. Latest quarterly / interim report
3. Latest strategy or investor presentation
4. Proxy / governance docs (US holdings)

Use `{TICKER}/INDEX.csv` or `{TICKER}/document-index.csv` as the document map when present.

## Research outputs

- Deep dive → `{TICKER}/research/deep_dive_{date}.md` + pending review copy
- Cross-check → `{TICKER}/research/cross_check_{date}.md`
- Download refresh → `{TICKER}/research/download_refresh_{date}.md`
- Daily scan → `_system/reviews/pending/scan_{date}.md` (under 800 words)

All outputs use the standard report footer (classification table, [HUMAN REVIEW], [PROPOSED MEMORY]).
